line_2: "And is it fit in hacqueton and mail
"And destly could he daunce, or pipe along the dale.

line_1: Now, to the waining Moon, the Nightingale
line_2: In doleful Ditties told her piteous Tale.
At evening brown, in woodland dale
Soft gurgling trills her amorous tale
Charms the forest with her tale;
Thee oft I met in Hertford's vale,
